#: ../../../topics/logging.rst:5
msgid "Logging"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/logging.rst:7
msgid ""
"Scrapy provides a logging facility which can be used through the :mod:"
"`scrapy.log` module. The current underlying implementation uses `Twisted "
"logging`_ but this may change in the future."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/logging.rst:13
msgid ""
"The logging service must be explicitly started through the :func:`scrapy.log."
"start` function."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/logging.rst:18
msgid "Log levels"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/logging.rst:20
msgid "Scrapy provides 5 logging levels:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/logging.rst:22
msgid ":data:`~scrapy.log.CRITICAL` - for critical errors"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/logging.rst:23
msgid ":data:`~scrapy.log.ERROR` - for regular errors"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/logging.rst:24
msgid ":data:`~scrapy.log.WARNING` - for warning messages"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/logging.rst:25
msgid ":data:`~scrapy.log.INFO` - for informational messages"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/logging.rst:26
msgid ":data:`~scrapy.log.DEBUG` - for debugging messages"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/logging.rst:29
msgid "How to set the log level"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/logging.rst:31
msgid ""
"You can set the log level using the `--loglevel/-L` command line option, or "
"using the :setting:`LOG_LEVEL` setting."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/logging.rst:35
msgid "How to log messages"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/logging.rst:37
msgid ""
"Here's a quick example of how to log a message using the ``WARNING`` level::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/logging.rst:39
msgid ""
"from scrapy import log\n"
"log.msg(\"This is a warning\", level=log.WARNING)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/logging.rst:43
msgid "Logging from Spiders"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/logging.rst:45
msgid ""
"The recommended way to log from spiders is by using the Spider :meth:"
"`~scrapy.spider.Spider.log` method, which already populates the ``spider`` "
"argument of the :func:`scrapy.log.msg` function. The other arguments are "
"passed directly to the :func:`~scrapy.log.msg` function."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/logging.rst:51
msgid "scrapy.log module"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/logging.rst:58
msgid ""
"Start the logging facility. This must be called before actually logging any "
"messages. Otherwise, messages logged before this call will get lost."
msgstr ""

