#: ../../../topics/logging.rst:66
msgid ""
"the minimum logging level to log. Available values are: :data:`CRITICAL`, :"
"data:`ERROR`, :data:`WARNING`, :data:`INFO` and :data:`DEBUG`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/logging.rst:70
msgid ""
"if ``True``, all standard output (and error) of your application will be "
"logged instead. For example if you \"print 'hello'\" it will appear in the "
"Scrapy log. If omitted, the :setting:`LOG_STDOUT` setting will be used."
msgstr ""

